  "blurb": "A four-bedroom villa set high in the ocean-view hills above Samui's north-west coast, looking out across the Gulf of Siam to the Angthong Marine Park, with a private pool, a yoga deck and gym, and daily chef and concierge service included.",
  "detail": "Perched in the hills above the island's north-west shore, this four-bedroom villa spans roughly 500 m² over two levels and sleeps up to eight guests. Open-plan living and dining rooms fold back onto a covered terrace, and the whole house is oriented toward a long, uninterrupted view over the water to the scattered peaks of the Angthong Marine Park.\n\nThe pool runs along the terrace edge, with sun loungers and a shaded lounge for the middle of the day. Beyond the main living areas, guests have a dedicated gym, a pool-table room and a quiet yoga space, giving the villa the range of a small private resort while keeping the feel of a home.\n\nEach of the four bedrooms has its own bathroom, with four full baths plus a guest powder room, and the interiors mix pale stone, timber and Thai detailing throughout. Air conditioning, fast Wi-Fi, a digital safe and a fully equipped kitchen with barbecue round out the practical side.\n\nThe nightly rate is fully serviced: daily housekeeping, twice-weekly linen changes, breakfast and lunch prepared by the villa chef, a multilingual manager on call, airport transfers and baby equipment on request. Cooking lessons, in-villa massage, tours, car and bike hire and chartered boat trips can all be arranged. A refundable security deposit is collected at check-in.",
